  "Gaussian elimination systematically uses elementary row operations to transform the augmented matrix into row echelon form, creating zeros below each pivot.": "",
  "Given the augmented matrix [[2, 4, 6], [1, 3, 5]], what should you do first to begin elimination using row 1 as the pivot row?": "",
  "Multiply R2 by 2": "",
  "Replace R1 with R1 - 2R2": "",
  "Swap R1 and R2": "",
  "Replace R2 with R2 - (1/2)R1": "",
  "To eliminate the entry below the pivot in column 1, subtract (1/2) times row 1 from row 2: R2 -> R2 - (1/2)R1, giving [[2, 4, 6], [0, 1, 2]].": "",
