  "The second row reads 0x + 1y = 3, so y = 3. Then back substitution gives x = 5 - 2(3) = -1.": "",
  "During Gaussian elimination, if the pivot element is zero, what should you do?": "",
  "Set the pivot to 1 and continue": "",
  "Delete the row entirely": "",
  "Swap the current row with a lower row that has a nonzero entry in that column": "",
  "Stop the algorithm; the system has no solution": "",
  "When the pivot position contains zero, you perform a row swap with a row below that has a nonzero entry in the same column. If no such row exists, move to the next column.": "",
