  "A pharmacist models drug interactions with three compounds (a, b, c) using the system a + b + c = 10, 2a + 3b + c = 18, and a + 2b - c = 4. After elimination she finds a = 2, b = 3, c = 5. She verifies by substituting into the third equation. What does she get?": "",
